# Localization Is Mandatory

## Intent

Localization is a default requirement across all client-facing MyClup surfaces. The monorepo must be designed for multilingual delivery from day one. A client-facing task is not done until localization impact is explicitly reviewed.

## Scope

Localization is mandatory for:

- Member mobile app (`apps/mobile-user`)
- Staff mobile app (`apps/mobile-admin`)
- Gym admin web (`apps/web-gym-admin`)
- Platform admin web (`apps/web-platform-admin`)
- Public website (`apps/web-site`)

## Mandatory Behaviors

- All client-facing text must come from translation resources or localized content models
- No hardcoded user-facing strings in screens, pages, or shared components
- Locale selection or locale detection must exist across all client apps
- Dates, times, numbers, currencies, and measurement units must be locale-aware
- User language preference must be modeled and respected across surfaces
- Shared translation keys and locale helpers live in shared packages, not per-app duplication
- Use shared locale utilities for dates, numbers, times, currencies, and units
- RTL readiness should be considered in component and layout design even if v1 is LTR-first

## Fallback Behavior

- Missing translations must fall back safely to the default locale
- Do not show empty strings or key names to users when a translation is missing
- Fallback order: requested locale → default locale → safe placeholder if defined
- Consent acceptance should record the locale shown to the user
- Do not ship new client-facing features without translation keys, locale formatting, and safe fallback behavior

## Content Types Requiring Locale Support

| Content type | Locale support |
|-------------|----------------|
| UI labels, buttons, messages | Translation resources |
| Legal, consent, policy text | Versioned per locale |
| Campaigns, notifications | Locale-aware variants |
| Chat templates, automated replies, chatbot content | Locale-aware variants |
| Gym-managed public content | Multilingual variants where applicable |
| Public website and discovery pages | Locale-aware SEO |
| API responses with user-facing text | Explicit locale in contract |

## Review Checklist

Before considering a client-facing task complete:

- [ ] No hardcoded strings in screens, pages, or shared components
- [ ] Translation keys exist for all new user-facing text
- [ ] Dates, times, numbers, currencies, units use locale-aware formatting
- [ ] User language preference is respected where applicable
- [ ] Missing translation fallback behavior is defined and tested
- [ ] Legal, consent, campaign, or chatbot content has locale variants if applicable
- [ ] RTL layout considerations noted for components that may need them later
